lation see [[RNA polymerase control by chromatin structure]] and table \"[[Histone#Histone modifications|Examples of histone modifications in transcriptional regulation]]\". Different physiological changes (e.g. deficiency of vitamin B12, etc.) are known to be associated with behavioural changes.[https://doi.org/10.1080/1028415X.2018.1548676] \n\n==See also==\n* [[Histone deacetylase]]s\n* [[Histone methyltransferase]]\n* [[Histone acetyltransferase]]\n* [[Nucleosome]]\n* [[Chromatin]]\n* [[PRMT4 pathway]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Histone-Modifying Enzymes}}\n[[Category:Epigenetics]]\n[[Category:Proteins]]\n", "name_user": "Dr Shreya A", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Histone-modifying_enzymes"}
{"title_page": "Bart\u0142omiej Lema\u0144ski", "text_new": "{{short description|Polish volleyball player}}\n{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Bart\u0142omiej Lema\u0144ski\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| nickname       = ''Leman''\n| nationality    = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland|Polish]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1996|3|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Warszawa]], [[Poland]]\n| height         = 2.16 m\n| weight         = 104 kg\n| spike          = 365 cm\n| block          = \n| position       = Middle blocker\n| currentclub    = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n| currentnumber  = 3\n| years          = 2012\u20132014<br>2014\u20132020<br>2014\u20132016\n| teams          = {{flagicon|POL}} Metro Warszawa<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]<br> \u2192 {{flagicon|POL}} [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska]] \n| nationalyears  = 2017\u2013\n| nationalteam   = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]]\n}}\n\n'''Bart\u0142omiej Lema\u0144ski''' (born 19 March 1996) is a Polish [[volleyball]] player, a member of [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]].\n\n==Career==\n===Clubs===\nIn 2014\u20132016 he was sent on loan to [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska]]. He was in top 10 best blockers of [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga]]. In 2016 he came back to [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]].<ref>[http://www.nowiny24.pl/sport/siatkowka/asseco-resovia/a/bartlomiej-lemanski-ma-217-cm-i-bedzie-gral-w-asseco-resovii,9974888/ ''Bart\u0142omiej Lema\u0144ski ma 217 cm i b\u0119dzie gra\u0142 w Asseco Resovii''] \u2013 nowiny24.pl \u2013 10-05-2016</ref>\n\n===National team===\nIn 2013 alongside  his national team he achieved bronze medal of [[2013 FIVB Volleyball Boys' U19 World Championship|2013 FIVB U19 World Championship]].<ref>[http://siatka.org/pokaz/2013-07-08-ms-kadetow-bialo-czerwoni-z-brazowym-medalem ''M\u015a kadet\u00f3w: Bia\u0142o-czerwoni z br\u0105zowym medalem''] \u2013 siatka.org \u2013 08-07-2013</ref> [[Ferdinando De Giorgi]] called Lema\u0144ski up to Polish national team for [[2017 FIVB Volleyball World League]].\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''National team'''\n** '''2013''' [[File:Silver medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2013 Boys' Youth European Volleyball Championship|CEV U19 European Championship]]\n** '''2013''' [[File:Bronze medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2013 FIVB Volleyball Boys' U19 World Championship|FIVB U19 World Championship]]\n** '''2013''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2013 European Youth Summer Olympic Festival|European Youth Olympic Festival]]\n** '''2019''' [[File:Silver FISU.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 2019 Summer Universiade|Summer Universiade]]\n===Individually===\n* '''2017:''' [[2017 Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner|Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/22782.html PlusLiga player profile]\n*[http://worldleague.2017.fivb.com/en/group1/teams/pol-poland/players/bartlomiej-lemanski?id=57264 World League player profile] at ''worldleague.2017.fivb.com''\n\n{{commons}}\n{{Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lemanski, Bartlomiej}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Warsaw]]\n[[Category:Polish men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:AZS Warszawa players]]\n[[Category:Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w players]]\n\n{{Poland-volleyball-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Polish volleyball player}}\n{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Bart\u0142omiej Lema\u0144ski\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| nickname       = ''Leman''\n| nationality    = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland|Polish]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1996|3|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Warszawa]], [[Poland]]\n| height         = 2.16 m\n| weight         = 104 kg\n| spike          = 365 cm\n| block          = \n| position       = Middle blocker\n| currentclub    = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n| currentnumber  = 3\n| years          = 2012\u20132014<br>2014\u20132020<br>2014\u20132016\n| teams          = {{flagicon|POL}} KS Metro Warszawa<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]<br> \u2192 {{flagicon|POL}} [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska]] \n| nationalyears  = 2017\u2013\n| nationalteam   = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]]\n}}\n\n'''Bart\u0142omiej Lema\u0144ski''' (born 19 March 1996) is a Polish [[volleyball]] player, a member of [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]].\n\n==Career==\n===Clubs===\nIn 2014\u20132016 he was sent on loan to [[AZS Politechnika Warszawska]]. He was in top 10 best blockers of [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga]]. In 2016 he came back to [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]].<ref>[http://www.nowiny24.pl/sport/siatkowka/asseco-resovia/a/bartlomiej-lemanski-ma-217-cm-i-bedzie-gral-w-asseco-resovii,9974888/ ''Bart\u0142omiej Lema\u0144ski ma 217 cm i b\u0119dzie gra\u0142 w Asseco Resovii''] \u2013 nowiny24.pl \u2013 10-05-2016</ref>\n\n===National team===\nIn 2013 alongside  his national team he achieved bronze medal of [[2013 FIVB Volleyball Boys' U19 World Championship|2013 FIVB U19 World Championship]].<ref>[http://siatka.org/pokaz/2013-07-08-ms-kadetow-bialo-czerwoni-z-brazowym-medalem ''M\u015a kadet\u00f3w: Bia\u0142o-czerwoni z br\u0105zowym medalem''] \u2013 siatka.org \u2013 08-07-2013</ref> [[Ferdinando De Giorgi]] called Lema\u0144ski up to Polish national team for [[2017 FIVB Volleyball World League]].\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''National team'''\n** '''2013''' [[File:Silver medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2013 Boys' Youth European Volleyball Championship|CEV U19 European Championship]]\n** '''2013''' [[File:Bronze medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2013 FIVB Volleyball Boys' U19 World Championship|FIVB U19 World Championship]]\n** '''2013''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2013 European Youth Summer Olympic Festival|European Youth Olympic Festival]]\n** '''2019''' [[File:Silver FISU.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 2019 Summer Universiade|Summer Universiade]]\n===Individually===\n* '''2017:''' [[2017 Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner|Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/22782.html PlusLiga player profile]\n*[http://worldleague.2017.fivb.com/en/group1/teams/pol-poland/players/bartlomiej-lemanski?id=57264 World League player profile] at ''worldleague.2017.fivb.com''\n\n{{commons}}\n{{Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lemanski, Bartlomiej}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Warsaw]]\n[[Category:Polish men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:AZS Warszawa players]]\n[[Category:Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w players]]\n\n{{Poland-volleyball-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Maister1921", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bart%C5%82omiej_Lema%C5%84ski"}
{"title_page": "List of Emmerdale characters (2020)", "text_new": "{{Short description|Emmerdale characters introduced in 2020}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Emmerdale'' characters (2020)}}\n''[[Emmerdale]]'' is a British soap opera first broadcast on 16 October 1972. The following is a list of characters that appear during 2020, by order of first appearance. All characters are introduced by the series producers Kate Brooks and Laura Shaw.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/emmerdale/news/a855492/emmerdale-three-new-producers/|title=Emmerdale confirms three new producers as Iain MacLeod's exit sparks major changes|last=Kilkelly|first=Daniel|date=24 April 2018|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=30 May 2018}}</ref> The first character to be introduced was [[#Harry Sugden|Harry Sugden]] (Brody and Teddy Hall), the son of [[Victoria Sugden]] ([[Isabel Hodgins]]) and [[Lee Posner]] (Kris Mochrie), followed by [[#Cara Robinson|Cara Robinson]] (Carryl Thomas). Additionally, multiple [[#Other characters|other characters]] appeared in 2020.\n==Cara Robinson==\n{{Infobox soap character\n|series = Emmerdale\n|name = Cara Robinson\n|portrayer = Carryl Thomas\n|introducer = Kate Brooks and Laura Shaw\n|years = 2020\u2013\n|first = Episode 8700 <br> {{Start date|df=y|2020|1|9}}\n|last = \n|classification = [[List of Emmerdale characters#Regular characters|Present; regular]]\n|sons = [[Nate Robinson (Emmerdale)|Nate Robinson]]\n|occupation = Accountant\n}}\n'''Cara Robinson''', portrayed by Carryl Thomas, made her first appearance on 9 January 2020. Cara is introduced as the mother of established character [[Nate Robinson (Emmerdale)|Nate Robinson]] (Jurrell Carter),<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/tv/itv-emmerdale-fans-shocked-nates-17779403.amp|title=ITV Emmerdale fans shocked by Nate's mum Cara Robinson|work=[[Liverpool Echo]]|accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref> who arrives in the village after receiving a voicemail from [[Moira Barton|Moira Dingle]] ([[Natalie J. Robb]]) about the affair Moira had with Nate.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/1227305/Emmerdale-spoilers-Nate-Robinson-Cara-Robinson-Cain-Dingle-exit-twist-ITV-video/|title=Emmerdale spoilers: Nate Robinsons' exit sealed in savage Cara and Cain Dingle twist?|work=[[Daily Express]]|accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref> Cara attempts to persuade Nate to leave the village with her, but he stays in Emmerdale. When Nate is accidentally shot by [[Cain Dingle]] ([[Jeff Hordley]]), she returns, suspicious of Cain and Moira. However, as he feels guilty over the affair, Nate covers for them by lying to Cara about what happened, saying he was shot by random farm hustlers.\n\nThe character's backstory states that Cara was in a relationship with Cain, but Cain's father, [[Shadrach Dingle]] ([[Andy Devine]]), detested the pair together due to his racism. Cara fell pregnant, and when Cain's mother [[Faith Dingle]] ([[Sally Dexter]]) found out, she persuaded her to leave. After having the baby, Nate, Cara made numerous attempts to contact Cain but Faith intercepted in an attempt to cover up what she had done.\n{{Clear}}\n\n==DI Malone==\n{{Infobox soap character\n|series= Emmerdale\n|name= DI Malone\n|portrayer= [[Mark Womack]]\n|introducer= Kate Brooks and Laura Shaw\n|years= 2020\u2013\n|first= Episode 8747 <br> {{Start date|df=y|2020|3|5}}\n|last=\n|classification= [[List of Emmerdale characters#Present characters|Present; regular]]\n|occupation= [[Detective Inspector]]\n}}\n'''DI Malone''', portrayed by [[Mark Womack]], made his first appearance on 5 March 2020.<ref name=\"Paul and Malone\" /> Malone is described as \"a police officer with a dark history\".<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1225570115795574784|title=CASTING NEWS: Mark Womack will be joining the cast of #Emmerdale. Mark will play DI Malone, a police officer with a dark history...stay tuned for his arrival in the Village in Spring 2020.|user=emmerdale|date=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n{{Clear}}\n\n==Paul Ashdale==\n{{Infobox soap character\n|series= Emmerdale\n|name= Paul Ashdale\n|portrayer= [[Reece Dinsdale]]\n|introducer= Kate Brooks and Laura Shaw\n|years= 2020\u2013\n|first= Episode 8777<br>{{Start date|df=y|2020|4|15}}\n|last=\n|classification= [[List of Emmerdale characters#Present characters|Present; regular]]\n|sons= [[List of Emmerdale characters (2019)#Vinny|Vinny]]\n}}\n'''Paul Ashdale<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/emmerdale/a32181931/emmerdale-spoilers-paul-ashdale-mandy-dingle-lies/?|title=Emmerdale's Paul Ashdale rumbles Mandy Dingle after her lies|first=Daniel|last=Kilkelly|date=17 April 2020|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]].}}</ref>, portrayed by [[Reece Dinsdale]], made his first appearance on 15 April 2020.<ref name=\"Paul and Malone\">{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/emmerdale/a30792078/emmerdale-cast-mark-womack-reece-dinsdale/|title=Emmerdale announces two new characters as Mark Womack and Reece Dinsdale join the cast|last=Lee|first=Jess|date=7 February 2020|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]]|accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref> Paul will have a connection to established characters [[Mandy Dingle]] ([[Lisa Riley]]) and her son, [[List of Emmerdale characters (2019)#Vinny|Vinny]] (Bradley Johnson).<ref name=\"her\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.her.ie/amp/entertainment/emmerdale-reveals-two-new-characters-joining-soap-spring-498646|title=Emmerdale reveals two new characters who are joining the soap this spring|work=[[her.ie]]|first=Keeley|last=Ryan|accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref> On his casting, Dinsdale commented \"I'm absolutely delighted to be joining the cast of ''Emmerdale''. Having recently directed a couple of episodes and seen at close quarters the superb work the cast, crews, and creatives produce, I can't wait to become part of the team once again \u2013 albeit in a different capacity.\"<ref name=\"Paul and Malone\" />\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n==Other characters==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|- valign=\"top\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Character\n! scope=\"col\" | Episode date(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Actor\n! scope=\"col\" | Circumstances\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Harry Sugden {{Anchor|Harry Sugden}}\n| 1 January 2020\u2013\n| Brody and Teddy Hall\n| The son of [[Victoria Sugden|Victoria Barton]] ([[Isabel Hodgins]]) and [[Lee Posner]] (Kris Mochrie).\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | DI Dent {{Anchor|DI Dent}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 27 January \u2013 4 March 2020\n| [[Linda Armstrong (actress)|Linda Armstrong]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Detectives investigating the murder of [[Graham Foster (Emmerdale)|Graham Foster]] ([[Andrew Scarborough]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/emmerdale/a30680483/emmerdale-fans-recognise-di-dent-linda-armstrong-the-royal/|title=This is why Emmerdale fans recognise newcomer DI Dent|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | DS Ward {{Anchor|DS Ward}}\n| [[Simon Delaney]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.itv.com/emmerdale/characters/ Characters and cast] at [[itv.com]]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0068069/fullcredits Characters and cast] at [[IMDb]]\n\n{{Emmerdale characters}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of Emmerdale characters|2020]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 2020|*, Emmerdale]]\n[[Category:2020 in British television]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Emmerdale characters introduced in 2020}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Emmerdale'' characters (2020)}}\n''[[Emmerdale]]'' is a British soap opera first broadcast on 16 October 1972. The following is a list of characters that appear during 2020, by order of first appearance. All characters are introduced by the series producers Kate Brooks and Laura Shaw.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/emmerdale/news/a855492/emmerdale-three-new-producers/|title=Emmerdale confirms three new producers as Iain MacLeod's exit sparks major changes|last=Kilkelly|first=Daniel|date=24 April 2018|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=30 May 2018}}</ref> The first character to be introduced was [[#Harry Sugden|Harry Sugden]] (Brody and Teddy Hall), the son of [[Victoria Sugden]] ([[Isabel Hodgins]]) and [[Lee Posner]] (Kris Mochrie), followed by [[#Cara Robinson|Cara Robinson]] (Carryl Thomas). Additionally, multiple [[#Other characters|other characters]] appeared in 2020.\n==Cara Robinson==\n{{Infobox soap character\n|series = Emmerdale\n|name = Cara Robinson\n|portrayer = Carryl Thomas\n|introducer = Kate Brooks and Laura Shaw\n|years = 2020\u2013\n|first = Episode 8700 <br> {{Start date|df=y|2020|1|9}}\n|last = \n|classification = [[List of Emmerdale characters#Regular characters|Present; regular]]\n|sons = [[Nate Robinson (Emmerdale)|Nate Robinson]]\n|occupation = Accountant\n}}\n'''Cara Robinson''', portrayed by Carryl Thomas, made her first appearance on 9 January 2020. Cara is introduced as the mother of established character [[Nate Robinson (Emmerdale)|Nate Robinson]] (Jurrell Carter),<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/tv/itv-emmerdale-fans-shocked-nates-17779403.amp|title=ITV Emmerdale fans shocked by Nate's mum Cara Robinson|work=[[Liverpool Echo]]|accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref> who arrives in the village after receiving a voicemail from [[Moira Barton|Moira Dingle]] ([[Natalie J. Robb]]) about the affair Moira had with Nate.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/1227305/Emmerdale-spoilers-Nate-Robinson-Cara-Robinson-Cain-Dingle-exit-twist-ITV-video/|title=Emmerdale spoilers: Nate Robinsons' exit sealed in savage Cara and Cain Dingle twist?|work=[[Daily Express]]|accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref> Cara attempts to persuade Nate to leave the village with her, but he stays in Emmerdale. When Nate is accidentally shot by [[Cain Dingle]] ([[Jeff Hordley]]), she returns, suspicious of Cain and Moira. However, as he feels gu